text: I’m saddened to learn of the death of James Whitlock, one of West Virginia’s hardworking miners. Coal miners are truly a family, and today, that family is united in sorrow. I join all West Virginians in sending our condolences and prayers to his family, friends and fellow miners.

Rev. Billy Graham ministered to presidents & parishioners alike, encouraging millions to deepen their walk with the Lord. His compassion, humility & faith inspire us all. We give thanks for his life and know that he will hear the words, “Well done, my good and faithful servant.”

I stand by @VP @POTUS in their efforts to make WV and our country great again. Saying Sen. Manchin voted no on tax cuts for West Virginians isn’t partisan, it’s the truth. Washington only sucks when members vote against their state’s interests.

I was not on the train headed to the GOP conference in Greenbrier County; I'm in Charleston right now. My prayers are with my colleagues and the driver of the truck hit -- praying that everyone is OK.
"We have ended the war on American energy -- and we have ended the war on beautiful clean coal. We are now, very proudly, an exporter of energy to the world." President Trump #SOTU @POTUS

There are 51 Republicans in the Senate, and it takes 60 votes to keep the government open, not a simple majority. That means Senate Democrats need to get on board to prevent a shutdown. They've asked for a CHIP reauthorization and the House has sent it to them -- twice. #WV3CHIP
We have 916 children in Cabell County who depend on CHIP. Cabell County includes my hometown of Huntington.  #WV3CHIP @SenSchumer #SchumerShutdown

21,391 West Virginia children depend on CHIP. That’s why I helped send the Senate a bill to reauthorize CHIP for six years – the longest renewal ever. Will Senate Democrats protect these children today? @SenSchumer #SchumerShutdown

Twelve years ago today, West Virginia lost 12 brave miners at Sago. We will never forget these husbands, fathers and sons, and our prayers are with their families as we reflect on one of the most difficult days in our state’s history.
I voted today to provide about $3 billion for CHIP, and I hope Senate Democrats will set aside partisan politics and vote to secure this critical program for West Virginia’s children.

disappointed that Senate Democrats won’t come to the table to work out a
long-term reauthorization agreement.

again to save this critical program. I thank House leadership for including the
